      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MUMDOGGIE (5) showed good early muster and fought on to finish second when resuming last start over 1207m at Oaklawn Park (Dirt). Has his share of ability. Hard to beat in this suitable race. MCCANN (10) produced a fair effort on debut last time out when 8 lengths from the winner in sixth at Keeneland Turf (Turf) over 1106m. Fitter and with the blinkers added is expected to be in the finish. IMPRACTICAL (6) was prominent at the turn and finished third last start at the first run back from a spell over 1207m at Fairgrounds (Dirt), beaten 3.5 lengths. This looks a sterner test than last time but on his best form he is capable of a big performance. HOVLAND (3) has not raced since his debut back on February 19 when he finished fourth over 1207m at Oaklawn Park (Dirt). Keep in mind with Lasix used for the first time. Something for the Multiples: ISLAND TOWN (1)",
